@agavra : Also, do you think we can have default scheduler release timeout of a few minutes? The scenario where the stages have been dispatched and one of the stages dies, leading to no data to the ancestor stages can be quite common.

At present since the default is -1, we accumulate these OpChains in the queue and never remove them. Would be great if these are removed in a few minutes by default given how commonly we could run into such issues.

